{
  "text": "(5) The PiCCO device may be not as accurate as reference technique in this setting (septicemic patients). Any bias and limits of agreement observed in this study could therefore be explained by the inaccuracy of the PiCCO system. The accepted clinical standard is still the intermittent thermodilution technique which in has its own inherent variability [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
